f(x,y)=3x+4y
0\le x \le1
-1\le y \le1 
 \ 3x + 4y \ = C \ 
 \ C \ 
 \ y = \frac{C}{4} - \frac{3}{4}x \ . 
 \ ( 0, -1 ) \ 
 \ C \ 
 \ 3 \cdot 0 \ + \ 4 \cdot (-1) \ = \ -4 \ , 
 \ ( 1 , 1 ) \ . 
 \ C \ 
 \ 3 \cdot 1 \ + \ 4 \cdot 1 \ = \ 7 \ , 
\max_{x,y} f(x,y) = \max_x \max_y f(x,y)
x \in [0,1], y \in [-1,1]
\min
\max_y f(x,y) = f(x,1) = 3x+4
\max_x (3x+4) = 3+4 = 7
